  "text": "Furthermore, although the paddy fields in the Sanjiang Plain is likely to increase continually and induce a cooling effect in the future, the sustainability of the irrigation rates may be limited by the availability of groundwater resources [CITATION_1] . If the groundwater resources become unsustainable, then the cooling effect may become the opposite and lead to food security issues [CITATION_2] . Therefore, besides the energy balance, we should also pay attention to the water balance when simulating or analyzing the climate effects caused by paddy expansion.",
